              "coded_information": [
                "GLASD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 9 cm diameter by 1 mm thick 6 Li-glass",
                "scintillator, viewed edge on by two RCA 8854",
                "five-inch photomultiplier tubes (PMTs)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Argon Resonant Transport Interaction Experiment",
                " (ARTIE) target consisted of a column of LAr of",
                "length 168 cm and diameter 25 mm, held at atmospheric",
                "pressure, and contained in a vessel constructed from",
                "standard components. A thick target experiment",
                " (3.3 atoms/b) optimized for the small cross sections",
                "in this energy region."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "TRN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Flight Path 13 (FP13) at the Lujan Neutron",
                "Scattering Center was used. FP13 has a total flight",
                "path of about 64 meters, allowing for excellent time",
                "of flight (TOF) energy resolution up to several",
                "hundred keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Combination of statistical and systematic",
                "uncertainties. The total systematic uncertainties on",
                "transmission and cross section are estimated for each",
                "energy point by using a toy Monte Carlo simulation",
                "where all relevant parameters are allowed to vary",
                "simultaneously around their central values. The",
                "resulting spreads within the 68th percentile around",
                "the central-value measurements of transmission and",
                "cross section are taken as the total systematic",
                "uncertainties."
              ]
            },
